# Auto-unlock the GNOME login keyring on tty login (no display manager).
# The auth line captures the login password; the session line starts
# gnome-keyring-daemon and unlocks (or creates, on a fresh machine) the
# login keyring with that password. This is what lets VS Code / libsecret
# use the org.freedesktop.secrets store without the "OS keyring is not
# available" warning. Lines are appended if missing (see deploy_patches).
auth optional pam_gnome_keyring.so
session optional pam_gnome_keyring.so auto_start
